Raila Odinga was officially endorsed as ODM presidential candidate at the party's National Delegates’ Convention on Friday. A charged crowd of Opposition leaders and their supporters shouted cheerfully after the announcement was made at Safaricom Stadium Kasarani in Nairobi. Raila waved at the people and smiled in acceptance. The nod by the ODM top decision-making organ comes just a week after the NASA Pentagon endorsed the former Prime Minister as the joint Opposition presidential candidate. The twin high profile endorsements give him the impetus to kick off a journey that he says was cut short through the “stolen election” in 2013.  Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka, ODM's Raila Odinga and Amani's Musalia Mudavadi the party's National Delegates Convention at Safaricom Stadium Kasarani in Nairobi, May 5, 2017. /EUGENE OKUMU The convention brought together delegates from all the 47 counties as its think-tanks put finishing touches on what they have termed the "unstoppable brand" of Raila. Raila 72, will face off against President Uhuru Kenyatta who is running for a second and final five-year term. This will be the fourth time Raila runs for president; he vied for president in 1997, 2007 and 2013. Read: NASA seeks billions as ODM unveils Raila Also read: Raila to appear as ODM candidate on ballot, not NASA 